You need to understand that aero is a monorepo
At the root, all directories are actually sub-projects of aero

# Files

- `aeroSW`: The code of aero that runs in the SW. It is powered by BareMux and whatever transports the user provides on their own proxy site.
  - `scripts`: Scripts for general maintenance of aero's SW code
  - `examples`: Examples for how to integrate aero into your proxy site. The files here actually copied to `aero.sh`'s build files to reduce duplicated code.
  - `extras`: Some JS files that make integrating aero into your proxy site more easier. The fiels here are copied for the same reasons.
